  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The proposed development, by reason of bulk, siting and appearance, would result in unacceptable harm to the street scene and local character, with an increasing sense of closure at this prominent corner plot and disruption to the symmetry on Peartree Gardens, notably given the location of the application site within the Becontree Estate. Therefore, the proposed development is contrary to: </p><p>- National Planning Policy Framework National Planning Policy Framework (NPPF) (DLUHC, 2023); </p><p>- Policy D1, D6 &amp; HC1 of the London Plan (March 2021); </p><p>- Policies CP2, CP3 &amp; CR2 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Core Strategy (July 2010); </p><p>- Policies BP2 &amp; BP11 of the Local Development Framework (LDF) Borough Wide Development Plan Document (DPD) (March 2011); </p><p>- Policies SP2/4, SPP6 &amp; DMD1/4/6 of the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Draft Local Plan: (Regulation 19 Submission Version, December 2021); </p><p>- The London Borough of Barking and Dagenham’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (February 2012).<br></p>"
